<body>
    <header class="doc-header">
        <div class="container">
            <h1>10th Marksheet Documentation</h1>
            <p>Secondary School Certificate - Education Board</p>
        </div>
    </header>

    <main class="container">
        <section class="doc-overview">
            <div class="card">
                <img src="/images/<%= data.image_data %>" alt="10th Marksheet Sample" class="doc-logo">
                <div class="doc-meta">
                    <p><strong>Issuing Authority:</strong> Respective Education Board (CBSE/State Board)</p>
                    <p><strong>Purpose:</strong> Academic record, higher education, employment</p>
                    <p><strong>Validity:</strong> Lifetime (can be reissued if lost)</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="application-process">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-list-ol"></i> Step-by-Step Application Process</h2>
            
            <div class="process-steps">
                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">1</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Determine Your Education Board</h3>
                        <p>Identify which board issued your marksheet:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>CBSE:</strong> For Central Board schools</li>
                            <li><strong>State Boards:</strong> Like Maharashtra, UP, Tamil Nadu etc.</li>
                            <li><strong>ICSE:</strong> For ICSE affiliated schools</li>
                            <li>Check your school's affiliation if unsure</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">2</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Collect Required Information</h3>
                        <p>Gather these details before applying:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Full name (as in school records)</li>
                            <li>Father's/Mother's name</li>
                            <li>School name with complete address</li>
                            <li>Year of passing and roll number</li>
                            <li>Registration number (if available)</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">3</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Choose Application Method</h3>
                        <p>Options to obtain marksheet:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>Original Copy:</strong> From your school (if recently passed out)</li>
                            <li><strong>Duplicate Copy:</strong> From education board (if lost/damaged)</li>
                            <li><strong>Online Verification:</strong> Digital marksheet through board portals</li>
                            <li><strong>Migration Certificate:</strong> If transferring to other board</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">4</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Apply for Duplicate (If Needed)</h3>
                        <p>For lost/damaged marksheets:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>Obtain application form from board office/website</li>
                            <li>Attach FIR (for lost marksheet) and affidavit</li>
                            <li>Include ID proof and passport photos</li>
                            <li>Pay applicable fees (varies by board)</li>
                            <li>Submit to regional board office</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">5</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Online Verification Process</h3>
                        <p>For digital verification:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li>CBSE: <a href="https://cbse.digitallocker.gov.in/" target="_blank">DigiLocker</a> or <a href="https://results.cbse.nic.in/" target="_blank">results.cbse.nic.in</a></li>
                            <li>State Boards: Respective board websites</li>
                            <li>Enter roll number and other details</li>
                            <li>Download digitally signed marksheet</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="step">
                    <div class="step-number">6</div>
                    <div class="step-content">
                        <h3>Receive Marksheet</h3>
                        <p>Processing and delivery:</p>
                        <ul>
                            <li><strong>School Collection:</strong> 1-2 months after results</li>
                            <li><strong>Duplicate Copy:</strong> 15-30 days after application</li>
                            <li><strong>Digital Copy:</strong> Instant download</li>
                            <li>Verify all details carefully upon receipt</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="video-guide">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-video"></i> Official Tutorial Video</h2>
            <div class="video-container">
                <iframe width="560" height="315" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/xsL6Ag3NrFk" title="10th Marksheet Application Process" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture" allowfullscreen></iframe>
            </div>
            <p class="video-caption">How to apply for duplicate 10th marksheet</p>
        </section>

        <section class="important-notes">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-exclamation-circle"></i> Important Information</h2>
            <div class="notes-grid">
                <div class="note-card">
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-rupee-sign"></i> Fees Structure</h3>
                    <p>CBSE Duplicate: ₹300 + postal charges<br>
                    State Boards: ₹200-500<br>
                    Migration Certificate: ₹150-300</p>
                </div>
                <div class="note-card">
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-file-alt"></i> Required Documents</h3>
                    <p>FIR (for lost marksheet)<br>
                    Notarized affidavit<br>
                    ID proof and address proof<br>
                    Passport photos (2-4)</p>
                </div>
                <div class="note-card">
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-university"></i> Board Contacts</h3>
                    <p>CBSE: <strong>1800-11-8002</strong><br>
                    Maharashtra: <strong>022-22041800</strong><br>
                    UP Board: <strong>0532-2467631</strong></p>
                </div>
                <div class="note-card">
                    <h3><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> Processing Time</h3>
                    <p>Duplicate: 15-30 working days<br>
                    Verification: 3-7 working days<br>
                    Urgent: Available at extra cost (some boards)</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="faq-section">
            <h2><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>Is digital marksheet valid for college admissions?</h3>
                <p>Yes, digitally signed marksheets from official board portals are legally valid as per UGC guidelines.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>Can I get my 10th marksheet after 10 years?</h3>
                <p>Yes, all education boards maintain permanent records. You can apply for duplicate marksheet anytime.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>What if there are errors in my marksheet?</h3>
                <p>Contact your school immediately. They will initiate correction process with the board (within 6 months of issue).</p>
            </div>
            <div class="faq-item">
                <h3>How to verify old marksheets online?</h3>
                <p>Most boards now have online verification systems. Check respective board websites or use DigiLocker.</p>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>

